        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29014",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "English is no known official language for Nigeria.\n\nPlease read the manual about which locales are available:\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.locale.appendix.html",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-02-23T01:38:17.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-02-23T01:40:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29015",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dewaldbotha",
                        "name": "dewaldbotha",
                        "displayName": "Dewald Botha",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi,\n\nI saw the list you have for the Zend Locale appendix - my issue however is that it is recorded in http:\/\/unicode.org\/cldr\/data\/diff\/supplemental\/languages_and_territories.html as an official language for Nigeria and that in your en.xml file in your locale data directory you have specific entries for Nigeria.\n\nNow, I might be wrong about it, but then there must be some other way of adding a xml file to add locale capability to the data.  So I'm guessing my question would be, what xml files\/entries would I have to make\/change in order to add en_NG as an option?\n\nThanks\nDewald Botha",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dewaldbotha",
                        "name": "dewaldbotha",
                        "displayName": "Dewald Botha",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-02-23T02:03:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-02-23T02:03:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29016",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "First:\nYou are referring to a draft which was never accepted by Unicode. Within the actual CLDR 1.6.1 this locale has not been accepted.\n\nSecond:\nYou can download the CLDR yourself and will see that this locale does not exist.\n\nThird:\nAs you may have mentioned this is Zend Framework and not Unicode. When you have a problem with the data from Unicode please ask at Unicode and not at Zend.\n\nForth:\nWe are not allowed to change this data because we are deploying it to other people. Doing so would be a legal problem.\n\nFifth:\nAs you may already imagine, I will not tell you how you can change Unicode's data as this also would be a legal problem. When you do this yourself it's on you :-)\n\nInstead of adding irregular data, which would be deleted with the next update, you should simply refer to the correct locale. Use 'en' for translation but 'ha_NG' for example for currency.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-02-23T04:17:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-02-23T04:17:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29073",
